<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"
xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word"
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">

<head>
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; padding: 40px; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 800px; color: #1f2937; }
        h1 { color: #111827; font-size: 28pt; border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb; padding-bottom: 10px; }
        h2 { color: #2563eb; font-size: 20pt; margin-top: 30px; }
        h3 { color: #4b5563; font-size: 16pt; margin-bottom: 5px; }
        p { font-size: 12pt; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 15px; }
        .image-container { text-align: center; margin: 20px 0; }
        img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; border: 1px solid #d1d5db; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
        .category { background-color: #f3f4f6; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
        ul { margin-top: 5px; }
        li { font-size: 12pt; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>RigPro Reports & Dashboards Overview</h1>
    <p>This document details the robust reporting infrastructure built into the RigPro platform. The system is divided into six core functional categories, dynamically consolidating operational, financial, and estimating data into actionable intelligence.</p>

    <h2>1. Executive Category</h2>
    <p>The Executive suite provides top-down visibility into the macro-health of the organization. Dashboards in this category are designed for presentation, easily converting into printable Management Board Reports (MBRs).</p>
    
    <div class="image-container">
        <img src="C:/Users/Scott/.gemini/antigravity/brain/df22f3c7-f182-4fa8-85b9-3dfdd865726c/exec_dash_1775338574994.png" alt="Executive Dashboard" />
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Executive Dashboard:</strong> Comprehensive overview featuring high-level KPIs, Revenue vs Forecast, and a composite Pipeline Health Index.</li>
            <li><strong>Pipeline Health Index:</strong> A composite score evaluating pipeline value, aging distributions, and win rates.</li>
            <li><strong>Revenue vs. Forecast:</strong> Actual won revenue plotted directly against forecasted bounds.</li>
            <li><strong>New vs. Returning Customer Revenue Split:</strong> Proportional division of revenue generated by new accounts versus returning stalwarts.</li>
            <li><strong>Win/Loss Analysis:</strong> Blended gross win rate indicating estimating efficiency trends.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>2. Pipeline Category</h2>
    <p>This category is the operational nucleus for the sales team, tracking active opportunities spanning from raw RFQ to finalized estimations.</p>
    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pipeline Dashboard:</strong> Aggregation and flow visualization of all incoming requests converting to open jobs.</li>
            <li><strong>Open Estimates:</strong> A structured aging snapshot of all estimates waiting for client approval.</li>
            <li><strong>Job Schedule:</strong> Advanced view into upcoming, scheduled, and active jobs.</li>
            <li><strong>Prospect Report:</strong> Targets leads who have pending activity but no historical "Won" jobs.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Customers Category</h2>
    <p>The core CRM reporting sphere, dedicated to tracking geographical mapping and unified interaction histories on an account-by-account basis.</p>

    <div class="image-container">
        <img src="C:/Users/Scott/.gemini/antigravity/brain/df22f3c7-f182-4fa8-85b9-3dfdd865726c/customer_dash_1775338592504.png" alt="Customer Dashboard" />
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Customer Activity Dashboard:</strong> An interactive, drag-and-drop dashboard to organize specialized widgets on specific accounts.</li>
            <li><strong>Neighborhood Report:</strong> Geospatial filtering connecting proximity maps to prospect data.</li>
            <li><strong>Jobs by Customer:</strong> Highlights total operational workloads and revenue volume driven by core clients.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>4. Finance Category</h2>
    <p>Focuses structurally on costs, profit margins, and specific line-item evaluations inside estimates (Labor, Equipment, Travel, etc.).</p>
    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Cost & Margin Analysis:</strong> Breakdown comparing initial sales numbers against estimated direct costs (Labor @ 0.6x, Equipment @ 0.7x, Hauling @ 0.85x).</li>
            <li><strong>Sales Adjustment Report:</strong> Line-item audit of internal adjustments made dynamically on won deals.</li>
            <li><strong>Labor Hours Quoted:</strong> Tracking allocated labor allocations and equivalent bill rates.</li>
            <li><strong>Discounts Given:</strong> Evaluation of margins sacrificed via estimator discounts.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>5. Historical Category</h2>
    <p>A repository for closed transactions, performance latency averages, and lost opportunity tracking.</p>
    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Inactive Requests:</strong> Post-mortem logging of RFQs marked Dead or Lost.</li>
            <li><strong>Lost Estimates:</strong> Post-mortem tracking of failed estimates by client and reason.</li>
            <li><strong>Historical Dashboard:</strong> Operational roll-ups.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>6. Activity Category</h2>
    <p>Tracks system utilization, employee productivity, and turnaround latencies.</p>
    <div class="category">
        <h3>Featured Reports</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Average Estimate Cycle:</strong> Velocity measurement from RFQ ingestion stage to Estimate Submission.</li>
            <li><strong>RFQ Response Time:</strong> Hard tracking of delay between client outreach and estimator contact.</li>
            <li><strong>Estimator Activity:</strong> Output mapping measuring raw volume of quotes generated and submitted per seat.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
